<paragraph id="8D1B36CEFFB45F053FBAE00CFE292B7C" blockId="23.[151,758,969,1890]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">
According to notes published by WENDELER (1955), the types of 
<taxonomicName id="4AA44D4DFFB45F053FD3E02CFD31289F" authority="(WENDELER, 1955)" baseAuthorityName="WENDELER" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[254,671,1129,1153]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Calocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">Calocerus simplex (WENDELER, 1955)</taxonomicName>
should be in his collection and in the collection of Franke. The collection of Wendeler was deposited in ZMHU, the collection of Franke was deposited in the collection of MNPD. A 
<typeStatus id="521F886CFFB45F053E21E0AFFEF0291C" box="[268,350,1258,1282]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4AA44D4DFFB45F053EABE0ACFDE3291F" baseAuthorityName="WENDELER" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[390,589,1257,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Calocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">Calocerus simplex</taxonomicName>
was not found in ZMHU, whereas 
<specimenCount id="9BA2FD47FFB45F053E42E14FFE54293C" box="[367,506,1290,1314]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">two syntypes</specimenCount>
were found in MNPD. The finding of the 
<typeStatus id="521F886CFFB45F053E70E16FFE17295C" box="[349,441,1322,1346]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4AA44D4DFFB45F053EF4E16CFF1D297F" authority="Wendeler" authorityName="Wendeler" authorityYear="1955" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Calocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">Calocerus simplex Wendeler</taxonomicName>
in MNPD revealed that they were identical with 
<taxonomicName id="4AA44D4DFFB45F053FBAE12FFE72299F" authority="IRMLER, 2012" authorityName="IRMLER" authorityYear="2012" box="[151,476,1385,1409]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="BFD0EADCFFB45F053FBAE12FFEEE299F" box="[151,320,1385,1409]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">Espeson simplex</emphasis>
IRMLER, 2012
</taxonomicName>
. IRMLER (2012) described the species on the base of specimens from the ZMHU, where it was deposited under the name 
<taxonomicName id="4AA44D4DFFB45F053D61E1EFFE2129FF" authority="WENDELER. Reviewing" authorityName="WENDELER. Reviewing" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="BFD0EADCFFB45F053D61E1EFFD5829DF" box="[588,758,1449,1473]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">Espeson simplex</emphasis>
WENDELER. Reviewing
</taxonomicName>
the 
<taxonomicName id="4AA44D4DFFB45F053EEBE18FFDDA29FF" box="[454,628,1481,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">Espeson species</taxonomicName>
and studying the material of ZMHU, IRMLER (2012) supposed that 
<taxonomicName id="4AA44D4DFFB45F053FBAE24FFEAF2A3F" box="[151,257,1545,1569]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="BFD0EADCFFB45F053FBAE24FFEAF2A3F" box="[151,257,1545,1569]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">E. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was a manuscript name given by Wendeler for a new undescribed species. After finding the 
<typeStatus id="521F886CFFB45F053DB5E26FFD5A2A5C" box="[664,756,1578,1602]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4AA44D4DFFB45F053F97E20CFED32A7F" authorityName="Wendeler" authorityYear="1955" box="[186,381,1609,1633]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Calocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="BFD0EADCFFB45F053F97E20CFED32A7F" box="[186,381,1609,1633]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">Calocerus simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in MNPD, it became clear that WENDELER (1955) described this species as 
<taxonomicName id="4AA44D4DFFB45F053DA0E22CFF482ABF" authorityName="Wendeler" authorityYear="1955" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Calocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="BFD0EADCFFB45F053DA0E22CFF482ABF" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">Calocerus simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Later he found that the species belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4AA44D4DFFB45F053FCEE2EFFE982ADF" authorityName="L.W.Schaufuss" authorityYear="1882" box="[227,310,1706,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BFD0EADCFFB45F053FCEE2EFFE982ADF" box="[227,310,1706,1729]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">Espeson</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but never published this transfer. So, 
<typeStatus id="521F886CFFB45F053FBAE28FFF5D2AFC" box="[151,243,1738,1762]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4AA44D4DFFB45F053E0CE28FFE7E2AFF" box="[289,464,1737,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="BFD0EADCFFB45F053E0CE28FFE7E2AFF" box="[289,464,1737,1761]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">Espeson simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
labelled by Wendeler are deposited in ZMHU and 
<specimenCount id="9BA2FD47FFB45F053E81E2AFFD992B1C" box="[428,567,1770,1794]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">two syntypes</specimenCount>
in MNPD. Thus, 
<taxonomicName id="4AA44D4DFFB45F053FB4E34FFE712B3F" authority="IRMLER, 2012" authorityName="IRMLER" authorityYear="2012" box="[153,479,1801,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="BFD0EADCFFB45F053FB4E34FFEEA2B3F" box="[153,324,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">Espeson simplex</emphasis>
IRMLER, 2012
</taxonomicName>
is identical with 
<taxonomicName id="4AA44D4DFFB45F053D8CE34FFE6D2B5F" authority="(WENDELER, 1955)" authorityName="Irmler" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="WENDELER" baseAuthorityYear="1955" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Espeson" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="BFD0EADCFFB45F053D8CE34FFF482B5F" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">Espeson simplex</emphasis>
(WENDELER, 1955)
</taxonomicName>
and becomes its objective homonymic synonym.
</paragraph>
